Perfect! I found your GitHub account (@bitwavee). Now let me create the repositories and set up all the project files. I'll create 2 repos:

1. **sales-quotation-api** (.NET Core + MSSQL)
2. **sales-quotation-app** (Flutter)

Let me provide you with complete **step-by-step instructions** to create and push these repos locally:

---

# 🚀 **Complete GitHub Setup Guide for Sales Quotation App**

## **Step 1: Create GitHub Repositories**

Go to **https://github.com/new** and create 2 repositories:

### **Repository 1: sales-quotation-api**
- **Name:** `sales-quotation-api`
- **Description:** REST API for field sales & quotation management (.NET 8 + MSSQL)
- **Visibility:** Public
- **Initialize:** ✅ Add a README file
- **Add .gitignore:** C#
- **Add license:** MIT

### **Repository 2: sales-quotation-app**
- **Name:** `sales-quotation-app`
- **Description:** Flutter mobile app for field sales & quotation management
- **Visibility:** Public
- **Initialize:** ✅ Add a README file
- **Add .gitignore:** Dart
- **Add license:** MIT

---

## **Step 2: Setup .NET Core Backend Repository Locally**

### **2.1 Clone and Navigate**

```bash
# Create workspace directory
mkdir ~/SalesQuotationProjects
cd ~/SalesQuotationProjects

# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/bitwavee/sales-quotation-api.git
cd sales-quotation-api
```

### **2.2 Create .NET Project Structure**

```bash
# Create solution
dotnet new sln -n SalesQuotationAPI

# Create class libraries
dotnet new classlib -n SalesQuotation.Domain
dotnet new classlib -n SalesQuotation.Application
dotnet new classlib -n SalesQuotation.Infrastructure

# Create API project
dotnet new webapi -n SalesQuotation.API

# Create test project
dotnet new xunit -n SalesQuotation.Tests

# Add projects to solution
dotnet sln add SalesQuotation.Domain/SalesQuotation.Domain.csproj
dotnet sln add SalesQuotation.Application/SalesQuotation.Application.csproj
dotnet sln add SalesQuotation.Infrastructure/SalesQuotation.Infrastructure.csproj
dotnet sln add SalesQuotation.API/SalesQuotation.API.csproj
dotnet sln add SalesQuotation.Tests/SalesQuotation.Tests.csproj
```

### **2.3 Add NuGet Dependencies**

```bash
# Navigate to each project and add packages

# Domain project
cd SalesQuotation.Domain
dotnet add package System.ComponentModel.Annotations
cd ..

# Application project
cd SalesQuotation.Application
dotnet add package AutoMapper
dotnet add package AutoMapper.Extensions.Microsoft.DependencyInjection
dotnet add package FluentValidation
dotnet add package FluentValidation.DependencyInjectionExtensions
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add package QuestPdf
cd ..

# Infrastructure project
cd SalesQuotation.Infrastructure
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design
cd ..

# API project
cd SalesQuotation.API
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer
dotnet add package System.IdentityModel.Tokens.Jwt
dotnet add package Swashbuckle.AspNetCore
dotnet add package Serilog
dotnet add package Serilog.AspNetCore
dotnet add package Serilog.Sinks.Console
dotnet add package Serilog.Sinks.File
dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration
cd ..

# Test project
cd SalesQuotation.Tests
dotnet add package xunit
dotnet add package Moq
dotnet add package xunit.runner.visualstudio
cd ..
```

---

